data.chText: 罗盘；罗经；指南针；罗盘仪
data.enText: an instrument for finding direction, with a needle that always points to the north

data.chText: 罗经方位点（东、南、西、北等）
data.enText: the points of the compass (= N, S, E, W, etc.)
an instrument with two long thin parts joined together at the top, used for drawing circles and measuring distances on a map
a range or an extent, especially of what can be achieved in a particular situation
the compass of a singer's voice (= the range from the lowest to the highest note that he or she can sing)

word_means: 理解；领悟；将…包围；成功办到
simple_means.memory_skill: com 共同 + pass 走；通过 → 共同走过的地方 →〔经过的〕范围

means: 理解；领悟；将…包围；成功办到

tr: drafting instrument used for drawing circles
an area in which something acts or operates or has power or control: "the range of a supersonic jet"
example: a piano has a greater range than the human voice
within the compass of this article
within the scope of an investigation
outside the reach of the law
in the political orbit of a world power
Do you comprehend the meaning of this letter?

tr: travel around, either by plane or ship

example: This writer attempts more than his talents can compass

value.def: A compass is an instrument that you use for finding directions. It has a dial and a magnetic needle that always points to the north.

example.ex: We had to rely on a compass and a lot of luck to get here.
example.tran: 我们不得不依靠指南针和不错的运气找到这儿来。

value.def: Compasses are a hinged V-shaped instrument that you use for drawing circles.
If something is within the compass of something or someone, it is within their limits or abilities.

example.ex: Within the compass of a normal sized book such a comprehensive survey was not practicable.
example.tran: 在通常一本书的篇幅中要作如此全面的调查不太实际。

trans: 方位圈；罗盘刻度盘；罗经盘
